# Desktop editor: interactive link styling

In the vault **capture** markdown editor (`NoteMarkdownEditor` / table cell editors under `[data-app-surface='capture']`):

- Any document range that **opens or creates** a vault note via **click**, **Mod-click**, or **Mod-Enter** must use the same **interactive link** presentation as the rest of that affordance: wiki links (`cm-wiki-link` / `cm-wiki-link--resolved` / `cm-wiki-link--unresolved`) and relative vault `.md` inline links (`cm-md-rel-link` / `cm-md-rel-link--resolved` / `cm-md-rel-link--unresolved` in [`App.css`](apps/desktop/src/App.css)).
- Do **not** leave **navigable** label or URL text styled as normal body copy while a sibling segment is the only red underlined “link” (users should not get a hidden click target).
- Markdown **bracket and paren marks** may stay muted like other syntax (see wiki `cm-md-wiki-bracket` pattern).

Authoritative behavior: [`specs/architecture/desktop-editor.md`](specs/architecture/desktop-editor.md) (wiki links and WL-6 relative markdown links).
